Then compute the universal Rezk type \bot {\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}} equipped with a map {\mathopen {}\left \{\bot \right \}\mathclose {}} \amalg _A {\mathbb {I}\times  A} \to  \bot {\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}.(Recall that Rezk types are defined by localising at just two maps.)

